=Write a short-form dialogue between two characters for a {{ $('Globals').first().json.NICHE_NAME }} YouTube Shorts channel.

=== CHARACTERS ===
{{ $('Globals').first().json.CHARACTER_A_NAME }} (A): {{ $('Globals').first().json.CHARACTER_A_PERSONALITY }}
{{ $('Globals').first().json.CHARACTER_B_NAME }} (B): {{ $('Globals').first().json.CHARACTER_B_PERSONALITY }}

=== AUDIENCE ===
{{ $('Globals').first().json.NICHE_AUDIENCE }}

=== THE CONCEPT TO BUILD (decided by the planner) ===
Concept: {{ $json.concept_title }}
Angle: {{ $json.angle }}
Brief: {{ $json.brief }}

=== SOURCE CHAPTER (full text, for grounding) ===
Book: {{ $json.book_title }} — by {{ $json.book_author }}
Chapter {{ $json.chapter_number }}: {{ $json.chapter_title }}

{{ $json.chapter_text }}

=== ANGLES TO AVOID (rejected on earlier attempts this run) ===
{{ JSON.stringify($json.avoid_angles) }}

=== RULES ===
- Build the concept described in the brief. Stay grounded in the chapter text — no invented facts.
- Exactly 4 to 7 lines, alternating speakers, starting with A.
- Total spoken length 55-75 words across all lines.
- Line 1 is the HOOK (6-12 words, from A): contradiction, personal callout, specific number, future shock, or pattern interrupt.
- Never start with 'Did you know', 'Have you ever', 'Imagine if', 'Scientists discovered', 'A new study'.
- Never mention the book, author, or that this is a summary.
- A voices doubt / the dumb-sounding question. B voices the insight, never lectures.
- Final line lands the thought. No CTA.
- Each line 1-2 sentences, punchy, sounds like real speech. 8th-grade reading level.
- Banned words: fascinating, incredible, mind-blowing, game-changer, literally (filler), unhinged, low-key, high-key.

=== OUTPUT (strict JSON, no markdown fences) ===
{
  "title": "YouTube Shorts title, <=60 chars, includes a searchable keyword",
  "oneLineSummary": "12-18 word neutral description of the core insight",
  "viralScore": 1-10,
  "onScreenCaption": "4-8 word bold opening text, different wording from the spoken hook",
  "keywords": ["3-5 searchable terms"],
  "lines": [ { "speaker": "A", "text": "the spoken line" } ]
}

